title: Missing teen may have crashed motorbike, SA searchers fear
text:
Missing teen Connor Wilson may have crashed motorbike, SA searchers fear Updated February 01, 2017 11:20:32 Map: Tantanoola 5280 
A wide search is being made of pine forests in the south-east of South Australia for a teenager who has been missing for almost a day. 
Police and State Emergency Services volunteers are searching for 16-year-old Connor Wilson, who left his home at Tantanoola early on Tuesday afternoon on his motorbike but failed to arrive at work in the evening. 
Police said the boy is about 180 centimetres tall and was wearing a black-and-white jumper, blue-and-grey motor cross pants, white boots and a black, silver and gold helmet. 
Two aircraft have now been called in to bolster the search effort, with authorities fearful the teenager has been involved in accident. 
The officer in charge of Millicent police, Peter Brown, said the air and ground search was checking plantations near the boy's home. 
"We're concentrating on a significant area of pine plantations. There is quite a large area to search," he said.
